ack\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xti1665702725693.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xti1665702725693.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xti1665702725693.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xti1665702725693\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      hold statements\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xti1665702725693__hold_statements_145191\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify whether statements remain open after a commit.\n </p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xti1665702725693__note_dw4_rvp_wbc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> This excludes statements for <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Select</span> requests\n      unless the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">slctenhance</span> option is also used.</div>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"xti1665702725693__topic_d47705e1_d47706e1_d47707e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xti1665702725693__d6720e17\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$<var class=\"keyword varname\">Mnemonic</var>_PARAMS = hold statements : on</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xti1665702725693__d6720e29\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$<var class=\"keyword varname\">Mnemonic</var>_PARAMS = hs : on</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xti1665702725693__topic_d31182e1_d31183e1_d31184e1_d31185e1_d31186e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d587261e89\">\n                        \n Use\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Applies to</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Mnemonic</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Connector Syntax</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">DB2 connector</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">DB2</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$DB2_PARAMS</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">ODBC connector</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">ODx</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$ODx_PARAMS</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">MS SQL Server connector</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">MSS</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$MSS_PARAMS</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">MySQL connector</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">MQL</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$MQL_PARAMS</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">PostgreSQL connector</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">PGS</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"xti1665702725693__table_8ba865d79d0e29d5d7d537a8b14b7507__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$PGS_PARAMS</code></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xti1665702725693__topic_d31187e1_d31188e1_d31189e1_d31190e1_d31191e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d587261e252\">\n                        \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xti1665702725693__p_d47720e1_d47721e1_d47722e1\">By default, when a commit is performed, the current hit list is truncated, and the statement used to retrieve it is discarded.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xti1665702725693__p_d47723e1_d47724e1_d47725e1\">If <code class=\"ph codeph\">hold statements</code> is set\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>, the current statement remains open, and the complete hit list remains\n        available, so it is possible to fetch the next items in the hit list. Additionally, for the\n        DB2 and MSS drivers, this option also controls whether cursors are closed when a commit or\n        rollback is done.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533910\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533910\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "hold statements Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 hold statements Specify whether statements remain open after a commit. Note: This excludes statements for Select requests unless the slctenhance option is also used. USYS$ Mnemonic _PARAMS = hold statements : on | off USYS$ Mnemonic _PARAMS = hs : on | off Use Applies to Mnemonic Connector Syntax DB2 connector DB2 USYS$DB2_PARAMS ODBC connector ODx USYS$ODx_PARAMS MS SQL Server connector MSS USYS$MSS_PARAMS MySQL connector MQL USYS$MQL_PARAMS PostgreSQL connector PGS USYS$PGS_PARAMS Description By default, when a commit is performed, the current hit list is truncated, and the statement used to retrieve it is discarded. If hold statements is set on , the current statement remains open, and the complete hit list remains available, so it is possible to fetch the next items in the hit list. Additionally, for the DB2 and MSS drivers, this option also controls whether cursors are closed when a commit or rollback is done. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}